Class SysErrorCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ethercis.servicemanager.common.def.SysErrorCode

    java.io.Serializable

    public final class SysErrorCode
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class holds an enumeration error codes.

    If you need new error code add it here following the same schema.

    The documentation is created by examining this class with it links.

      • isOfType

        public final boolean isOfType(SysErrorCode baseCode)
        Returns 'true' if this error code is a 'child' of the error code specified in baseCode. It follows the name convention of the error code. For example USER_SECURITY_AUTHENTICATION_DENIED would be of type (logonservice it is a subtype) of USER_SECURITY_AUTHENTICATION If one of the error codes code name is null, false is returned.
        Parameters:
        baseCode - the base ErrorCode to check against. If null, false is returned.
        Returns:
